It is 'also ordained and assented to by all the Companions of the “ fferschip ” that four good and loyal members of the said Company be elected Wardens to rotect the said ordinance well and loyally, and that they be sworn before the said company, and who shall loyally collect and preserve to the common benefit of the whole Company all the services and doles, small and great, as they arise, and that no money shall be delivered by the said Wardens toan of the Company except in payment of his share.
